Contact Form Backend with Node.js & Nodemailer






A simple, reusable contact form backend built with Node.js, Express, Nodemailer, and dotenv. Handle submissions from static websites and send them directly to your email.

Features

Send emails securely using Gmail and Nodemailer

Modern, responsive contact form frontend

Displays success/error messages dynamically

Works with multiple static websites

Easy setup with environment variables

Demo / Screenshot

Open the form locally at http://localhost:5000 after starting the server.

Installation

Clone the repository

git clone https://github.com/chami254/CONTACT-FORM.git
cd CONTACT-FORM


Install dependencies

npm install


Create a .env file in the project root:

EMAIL_USER=your_email@gmail.com
EMAIL_PASS=your_gmail_app_password
PORT=5000


Use a Gmail App Password if you have 2FA enabled.

Start the server

node server.js

Usage

Place your static site in the public/ folder

Ensure your form posts to /send with these fields:

name

email

message

Test sending messages—they’ll arrive at the email set in mailOptions.to

Project Structure
CONTACT-FORM/
├─ public/           # Static frontend files (HTML, CSS, JS, screenshots)
├─ server.js         # Express server & Nodemailer logic
├─ package.json
├─ .env              # Environment variables (not committed)
└─ README.md

Security Notes

Do not commit your .env file

For Gmail, use an App Password

Backend can be reused for multiple sites; just customize the frontend form

